### 5.4 Four Gates Enforcement

Apply to every test as it is written. **Violations are blocking.**

**Gate 1 — Element Selection:**
```
IF using text content as primary selector (getByText, innerText matching)
  → VIOLATION: Use stable selector from the agreed strategy
  → Preference: data-testid > id > aria-*/name > structural
IF using deeply nested CSS path without human approval
  → WARNING: Flag as fragile, confirm with human
```

**Gate 2 — Test Isolation:**
```
IF test depends on state from previous tests
  → VIOLATION: Each test must set up its own state
IF test leaves state without cleanup
  → VIOLATION: Add cleanup in afterEach or use truncation
```

**Gate 3 — Determinism:**
```
IF test uses manual timeouts (waitForTimeout, setTimeout)
  → VIOLATION: Use framework auto-wait or explicit condition waits
IF test depends on external services without mocking
  → VIOLATION: Mock external dependencies or use test doubles
```

**Gate 4 — Scope Appropriateness:**
```
IF testing internal logic without user interaction
  → VIOLATION: Use unit test instead
IF testing single component in isolation
  → VIOLATION: Use component test instead
```

**Agent must detect violations and execute recovery automatically without asking permission.**

### 5.5 Exit Gate — Build

```
IF any flow's tests not written
  → STOP. Complete remaining flows.

IF any test fails
  → STOP. Fix or report to human.

IF Four Gates violations exist in any written test
  → STOP. Fix violations.

VALID: Continue to Step 6
```

