## Common Rationalisations (FORBIDDEN)

**Agent must refuse these justifications with mandatory counter-responses:**

| User Says | Agent Must Respond |
|-----------|--------------------|
| "E2E covers it, skip unit tests" | "No. E2E verifies integration. Unit tests drive design. Writing unit tests first." |
| "Just add a small wait to fix flakiness" | "No. Waits hide timing bugs. Finding root cause." |
| "Tests pass in sequence, that's fine" | "No. Tests must pass independently. Adding proper setup." |
| "Testing the API call proves it works" | "No. Test user-visible outcome, not implementation." |
| "We don't need E2E for this" | "If the feature has user-facing flows, it needs E2E verification." |
| "Skip the manifest, just write tests" | "No. The manifest ensures traceability to acceptance criteria. Plan first, build second." |
| "Use getByText, the text won't change" | "Text is content, not contract. Use stable selectors from the agreed strategy." |

**If user persists:** Add a note to the relevant planning document recording the override and the reason given. Then continue.

